17 SUMMARY
1188 This amendment makes the following changes to the bill.
19 1. It changes the requirement that a hospital determine a patient's eligibility for
20 financial assistance and inform the patient of the eligibility determination within 30 days
21 from the date a completed application is submitted to within 45 days from the date a
22 completed application is submitted.
23 2. It changes the requirement for hospitals to provide physical copies of the plain
24 language summary, the financial assistance program application and any application
25 instructions in conspicuous locations within the hospital, including admission, registration
26 and waiting areas, to a requirement that hospitals provide in these conspicuous locations
27 information as to how a patient can access physical copies of these documents.
28 3. It changes the requirement that a hospital offer a patient with a documented family
29 income that does not exceed 400% of the federal poverty level a payment plan that requires
30 monthly out-of-pocket payments that do not exceed 3% of the patient's monthly family
31 income that is not exempt from attachment or garnishment under state law to a requirement
32 that the offered payment plan not exceed 4% of that income.
33 4. It provides that the date by which a hospital is required to provide an online option
34 through which an applicant may file an application for charity care is July 1, 2028.
35 5. It adds an appropriations and allocations section.
36 6. It changes the effective date of the legislation from January 1, 2026 to July 1, 2026.
